#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: money-multisection
---

# std/money multi-section namespace

Regression for the JS backend. `std/money` is a markdown module split across
sections: the `Currency` / `Money` constructors are declared under one heading
and `defaultCurrencies` / `currencyOf` under another. Each section is emitted as
a separate `_ssc_mergeDeep` IIFE, so the second section referenced the first
section's `Currency` constructor across an isolated scope and threw
`ReferenceError: Currency is not defined` on Node. A later section must re-bind
the earlier section's members from the live namespace.

`currencyOf` reaches `Currency` two ways — via `defaultCurrencies` (which builds
`Currency` values) and via its `getOrElse` fallback `Currency(code, 2, code)`.

[currencyOf](std/money.ssc)

```scalascript
println(currencyOf("PLN").symbol)
println(currencyOf("PLN").scale)
println(currencyOf("JPY").scale)
println(currencyOf("XXX").symbol)
println(currencyOf("XXX").scale)
```
